Description:
Want to make a great impact with a fast-paced tech scale-up in robotics? Join our enthusiastic and passionate software development team and be in the forefront of innovation!

What do you do?

As a DevOps Engineer, you will be responsible to keep our local IT infrastructure and Cloud environment (AWS) up-and-running. This includes, amongst other:

Daily management and development of our internal and external services;
Enabling our software developers by providing the necessary tooling and platforms to run their software in an automated and reliable way in the cloud and on premise;
Setting up the Continuous Integration / Continuous Deployment pipeline using technologies (such as e.g. GitLab, Kubernetes, …);
Constant monitoring of our services and the market to be sure that we are operate with the latest versions and the best tools (in balance with the cost);
Work closely with our embedded, mobile and backend developers to continuously improve the systems and deliver support where needed;
Assist on an ad-hoc basis with office operations (limited).

Who are you?

You have experience with Cloud services. Experience with AWS would be a big plus;
You have a clear idea when (not) to use Kubernetes, Docker…;
Ansible, Grafana, Prometheus, GitLab,... have no secrets for you;
We love Java and its many frameworks, so good knowledge of Java would be a big plus;
You are eager to learn, have a passion for technology and are always up to date with the latest evolutions;
You have excellent communication skills in English.

What do we offer?

The opportunity to drive innovation in the field of robotics (read our masterplan for more information: www.toadi.com/master-plan);
An enthusiastic and passionate team of (senior) engineers. You will work with the best!
A flexible working environment: home office / remote work and flexible working hours;
Wide benefits and compensation package in line with your experience;
Numerous office perks: delicious coffee, tea & fresh orange juice, fresh fruit, French fries or delicious Bowls on Friday and much more!

Job Types: Full-time, Permanent

Benefits:

Company computer
Eco vouchers
Food allowance
Internet reimbursement
Retirement plan
Work from home

Schedule:

Day shift
Flexible hours

Supplemental Pay:

13th month salary
Vacation money

Work Remotely:

No
